        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "> That's a bold assumption.\n\nFortune favors the bold. \n\n> First, this can only ever work for builtin container types because user defined containers may return arbitrary objects on item getting.\n\nOf course I am meaning **only** builtin types. I would say following this is only possible for:\n* only bultin types - list, set, dict, frozenset and frozen dict\n* only variable accesible from cython hence cdef variables and cdef function arguments\n\nIs it possible in a reasonablr way to change cython variables outsice cython in meaningful way? I suppose not but I can be wrong.",
